<arggraph id="micro_k010" topic_id="public_broadcasting_fees_on_demand" stance="pro">
  <edu id="e1"><![CDATA[Considering what's on television these days,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e2"><![CDATA[it would be appropriate to only have those people pay who actually (want to) follow the programming.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e3"><![CDATA[In some cases there are only shows for older generations on at prime times,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e4"><![CDATA[so why then should everyone pay for this?]]></edu>
  <edu id="e5"><![CDATA[By now you have advertising on all channels,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e6"><![CDATA[so there's no advantage for the current paying viewers of the public broadcasters.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e7"><![CDATA[Nevertheless one has to point out that there'd probably be way fewer stations]]></edu>
  <edu id="e8"><![CDATA[if it weren’t the whole of Germany that’s obliged to pay.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e9"><![CDATA[That shouldn't be an issue though,]]></edu>
  <edu id="e10"><![CDATA[given the sheer number of programmes and stations that essentially show the same things anyway.]]></edu>
